                    {
                        "comments": [],
                        "name": "Data transformation",
                        "protocolType": {
                            "comments": [],
                            "annotationValue": "Data transformation",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>Raw intensity values were quantile-normalized separately for ions acquired in positive and negative modes. For further analysis, the data from the 2 acquisition polarity modes were combined in 1 table and filtered as follows: only annotated ions were retained; ions annotated to 13C-compounds only were removed; for each metabolite, only the ion with the annotation considered most likely was retained (either the ion with highest correlation with the total ion current, or the ion with the largest mean intensity across samples).</p>",
                        "uri": "",
